Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_design(25.10)                                        check_design(25.10)

Name
       check_design  - Checks that all prerequisites to run all or part of the
       hierarchical or block implementation flow are met

Syntax
       check_design

       [-help]

       [-id <violation_id>]

       [-out_file <fileName>]

       {[-type {library netlist  synthesis  power_intent  timing  hierarchical
       pin_assign budget assign_statements extract_rc place opt cts route sig-
       noff  all}  |-type_3d  {db  tech_lib  netlist power_intent timing place
       floorplan route report_only all}}[-format {table detail}]]

       [-no_check ]}

       Checks that all prerequisites to run all or part of the hierarchical or
       block implementation flow are met.

       The check_design command checks the preconditions for major flow  steps
       before  they  are run.  If there are errors identified by check_design,
       the current script will stop.check.  Note that output  to  console  and
       log  file  is  controlled by message display limit.  A complete list of
       errors is dumped to -out_file.

       Some examples of problems that will cause design  checks  to  fail  in-
       clude:

              * Cells used in the design that cannot be legally placed

              * Tracks misaligned with some or all cell pins

              * In  advanced  processes,  power nets that cannot be colored in
                the expected pattern once cells are placed

              * Cell rows that are unblocked for placement but where pin  lay-
                ers are obstructed

              * Cell  rows that are unusable due to orientation and power rail
                misalignment

              * Cells instantiated in the netlist that have  no  timing  model
                defined

              * Tracks blocked by power grid spacing constraints

              * Instances not covered by a true timing path in any view

              * ILM model with no clock tree defined

              * No hold fixing cells are specified and delay cells are not us-
                able

              * No  clock  inverters,  buffers, clock gates or logic cells are
                specified and the library cells are not usable for clock trees

              * CTS cannot balance all skew groups without  increasing  inser-
                tion delay

              * Preserved  nets  and cells in the clock tree that will violate
                other constraints because they cannot be resized or buffered.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes a list  of  parameters,
              their usage, and their defaults.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man check_design.

              No other args allowed with -help

       -format {table detail}
              Specifies the format for reporting violations.

              * table: Prints the results in the table format.

              * detail: Prints details of violations.

       -id <violation_id>
              Specifies the violation IDs.

       -type  Specifies the category of the flow to be checked.

              The  intent  is to run check_design before each of the operation
              in the list. Each of the categories run several  checks  related
              to that operation.

              * library:  Checks for the integrity of the library and for cor-
                rect binding of all design instances to library cells  or  RTL
                modules. Individual checks are as follows:

                * For  physical_only  library, check_design will flag libcells
                  that have only LEF but no .lib representation.

                *

                  For logical_only library, check_design  will  flag  libcells
                  that have only .lib but no LEF representation.

              * netlist:  Checks  the  netlist  integrity  at any point in the
                flow.

                *

                  For undriven netlist, check_design will check  the  list  of
                  input/inout  hpins/pins  with no driver on the net connected
                  to it (driver can be input port or output hpin/pin).

                *

                  For multiple_driver netlist,  check_design  will  check  the
                  list  of  input/inout  pins  or output/inout ports with more
                  than one driver on their net)

                *

                  For unloaded netlist, check_design will check the  input/in-
                  out  ports  or  output  hpins/pins with no load (input/inout
                  pins) in their fanout or hinsts/insts that have nothing con-
                  nected to any output pin)

                *

                  For constant netlist, check_design  will  check  the  output
                  ports  or input pins/hpins that are driven by a logical con-
                  stant 0/1.

                *

                  For feedthrough netlist, check_design will check the hinsts,
                  where every output pin is directly driven by an  input  pin,
                  w/o any logic in between).

                *

                  For  empty_modules,  check_design will reports empty modules
                  in the design.

              * synthesis: Checks the following violations

                * The design has unresolved references.

                * Insufficient number of latches available.

                * Insufficient number of clock gates available.

                * Design has combinational loops.

              * power_intent: Checks related to MSV setup including power  do-
                main/fence checks.

              * timing:  Performs  checks  related  to timing setup integrity.
                This check is run prior to running any operation that requires
                timing information.  Note:  The  check_timing  command  should
                still be used for more exhaustive timing checks.

              * hierarchical:  When  you  use the hierarchical, pin_assign, or
                budget options with the -type parameter, the check_design com-
                mand checks for hierarchical partitions in the design. It per-
                forms checks related  to  the  hierarchical  flow.  This  type
                checks if the partition has a fence and if the fence is inside
                the  core boundary. If not, it displays an error message. This
                check is run before running hierarchical design operations.

              * pin_assign: Checks related to pin assignment for  partitioning
                flows. This check is run before pin assignment.

              * budget:  Checks  related  to  time  budgeting for partitioning
                flows. This check is run before timing budgeting.

              * assign_statements: Performs checks for the netlist for  assign
                statements.  This  check is run before exporting a netlist for
                signoff.

              * extract_rc: Checks if the lef layer map is  correctly  defined
                and  outputs  warning/error  when  it finds issues such as lef
                layer not defined, QRC layer not defined.  Also  performs  the
                FTV subcircuit file check.

              * place:  Checks related to placement such as PG rail alignment,
                pin access issues, missing followpin in the rails of  standard
                cells, misaligned well tap cell, and missing termination cell.
                This check is run before placement.

              * opt:  Checks related to optimization such as checks for avail-
                able cells. This check is run before optimization.

              * cts: Checks related to clock  tree  definition  such  as  con-
                straint  targets  and  route types. This is run before cts but
                after creating the clock tree spec. This check cannot run with
                pre-cts Innovus DB (just after place_opt_design). You need  to
                set  CCOpt  option  (target  skew, target trans, etc) and also
                need to load the CCOpt spec file.

              * route: Checks related to routing such  as  congestion,  place-
                ment,  and  pin  access  issues. The -type route cannot be run
                with pre-placed DB. This check is run before  routing.  It  is
                useful  to  run  check_drc ahead of time so the design markers
                are up to date. Also checks if the probe pin is logically con-
                nected, directly, to the SI pin. If not, the tool will show  a
                violation  marker on the probe marker. The violation marker is
                of the same size and the same location as the probe marker.

              * signoff: Checks related to the  signoff  activities  including
                extraction and ECOs. This check is run before TSO. To use this
                types,  you  need  to  set the Tempus path, else the tool will
                give an error.

              * all: Checks related to all categories.

              Note: -type or -no_check is required (except  when  using  -help
              argument)

       -no_check
              Do  not  run any checks, echo the error messages associated with
              the checks that would  be  run  for  the  specified  -type.  Run
              check_design -no_check to see the list of checks.

               -type  or  -no_check is required (except when using -help argu-
              ment)

       -out_file <fileName>
              Specifies the output report file. Contents dumped to  this  file
              are in the Tcl format.

              Sourcing  this  file  will create a TCL dictionary of the viola-
              tions found by check_design.

       -type_3d {db tech_lib netlist power_intent timing place floorplan route
       all}}
              Specifies the 3DIC design categories to check. You  can  specify
              single or multiple categories

              * db

                * Checks if the die is defined in the design stack file

                * Checks if the 3D DB setup correct

              * tech_lib

                * Checks the library integrity and corrects binding

                * Checks all timing lib wh

              * netlist

                * Checks the library integrity and corrects binding

              * power_intent

                * Checks  related  to  MSV  setup including power domain/fence
                  checks.

                * Checks related power domain bind to correct design

              * timing

                * Performs checks related to timing setup integrity.

              * place

                * Checks related to placement such as pin alignment

              * floorplan

                * Checks related to floorplanning

              * route

                * Checks related to routing

              * all

                * Checks all categories

Examples
              * The following example shows the usage of the -out_file option:

       > check_design -type "place cts route" -out_file checks.tcl

       *** Summary of all messages that are not suppressed in this session:

        Severity ID Count Summary

        WARNING CHKCTS-16 1 Preferred routing layers for route_type ...

        ERROR CHKCTS-1 3 CTS maximum transition target must be se...

        ERROR CHKCTS-10 1 Route type(s) %s used for trunk or top c...

        WARNING CHKCTS-21 1 Clock logic cells are not specified for ...

        WARNING CHKCTS-46 1 Clock logic cells are not specified for ...

        WARNING NRIG-1323 65 Net %s has bottom preferred routing laye...

       > source checks.tcl

       > dict keys $design_checks

        cts route

       > dict keys [dict get $design_checks place]

       CHKCTS-1 CHKCTS-10 CHKCTS-16 CHKCTS-21 CHKCTS-46

       # Each check as the following keys

       > dict keys [dict get [dict get $design_checks cts] CHKCTS-1]

       severity count violations

       # For information regarding the check, use get_message:

       > get_message -id CHKCTS-1 short

       CTS maximum transition target must be set to a numeric  value  for  de-
       lay_corner %s and delay_type %s for clock_tree %s and net_type %s.

       # To query the violations, use the check dictionary:

       > dict get [dict get [dict get $design_checks cts] CHKCTS-1] violations

       {dc_0.9v_125c late clk top}

       {dc_0.9v_125c late clk trunk}

       {dc_0.9v_125c late clk leaf}

